SCIENTIFIC_NAME: Willaertia De Jonckheere, Dive, Pussard & Vickerman, 1984
AUTHOR: De Jonckheere, Dive, Pussard & Vickerman

QUALIFICATION: Whitmore's description is inadequate to determine whether Trimastigamoeba is the same organism as Willaertia or one of the Naegleria spp. that have more variable flagellar number; Bovee's illustrations of amoebae and flagellates he assigned to this genus do not clarify this question (see Robinson et al. 1989 for discussion)
AUTHOR: Whitmore
PUB_PUB_TITLE: Studien uber Kulturamoben aus Manila.
PUB_PUB_FORMATTED: Whitmore, E.R. 1911. Studien uber Kulturamoben aus Manila. Archiv für Protistenkunde 23: 81-95

QUALIFICATION: Singh & Hanumaiah's description is inadequate to determine whether Tetramastigamoeba is the same organism as Willaertia (in which case it would be the valid name -- but see also Trimastigamoeba Whitmore 1911) or one of the Naegleria spp. that are initially tetraflagellate and can divide in the flagellate stage (see Robinson et al. 1989 for discussion). Singh & Hanumaiah also described a mechanism for the origin of flagella that is not consistent with the biogenesis of any other eukaryotic flagella
